f = q\\\"def triple(n: Int): Int = n * 3\\\"\\n        |    val term: Term = q\\\"List(1, 2, 3).map(triple)\\\"\\n        |    val tpe: Type = t\\\"Either[String, Int]\\\"\\n        |    val pattern: Pat = p\\\"Some(value)\\\"\\n        |\\n        |    val termShape: String = term match {\\n        |      case Term.Apply(Term.Select(_, Term.Name(methodName)), List(Term.Name(argumentName))) =>\\n        |        methodName + \\\":\\\" + argumentName\\n        |      case other => other.productPrefix\\n        |    }\\n        |    val typeShape: String = tpe match {\\n        |      case Type.Apply(Type.Name(name), arguments) => name + \\\":\\\" + arguments.size\\n        |      case other => other.productPrefix\\n        |    }\\n        |    val patternShape: String = pattern match {\\n        |      case Pat.Extract(Term.Name(name), List(Pat.Var(Term.Name(value)))) => name + \\\":\\\" + value\\n        |      case other => other.productPrefix\\n        |    }\\n        |\\n        |    List(method.name.value, method.paramss.head.head.name.value, termShape, typeShape, patternShape)\\n        |  }\\n        |}\\n        |\\n        |RuntimeQuasiquoteProgram.run()\\n        |\\\"\\\"\\\".stripMargin\\n\\n    toolBox.compile(toolBox.parse(source)).apply().asInstanceOf[List[String]]\\n  }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778133089331}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Analyzing test compilation issues**\\n\\nI’m diving into some challenges after building the jaCoCo test, where the macro class in the library is involved only during test compile, not at runtime unless the test explicitly invokes the compiler. The Toolbox tends to slow down over sixty seconds, so I’m wondering if using the Scala Reflect Toolbox to prewarm could help. However, that might not be effective.\\n\\nI’m thinking about using Scala's Global in a separate process. Individual tests seem to stay below sixty seconds, but I could spawn an external scalac, though this might also exceed the time limit. Simplifying the quasiquotes might streamline things significantly. I need to create a dedicated test class for ReificationMacros that efficiently triggers all necessary compile-time macros during the testing. It feels like I’m zeroing in on the core issues.\\n\\n**Exploring test coverage and macros**\\n\\nI’m considering whether including direct quasiquotes and removing the Toolbox could allow the test to pass, but I wonder about dynamic access. Perhaps a dynamic report could be generated by the agent during compileTestScala. I’m also thinking about the remaining call sites from ReificationMacros, since macros during test compilation might not be captured by the agent. It seems the TCK likely runs javaTest with the native-image agent, rather than during compilation. I need a test that invokes the macro at runtime, but that could be challenging with the Toolbox's speed limitations.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc284f5dc8819c88b749e83a00480a\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_Chg3OTNCavr-D8fNr92rL-ZMx44DQcP3gAZZ7fXBll5yM7GbVgfTC7Z5jQ6gFeQMqPwdohxiyad_DPDHispX9Vfndk8FCEEKKHpaI3QoDtGuzErggyro3C2TqqqIwQLj5KiRiYRkhEK78ssTWJchKKbSB-Khyuzok1B4PcXLR4B46lGYG6Y-J4Ucg9PKXhcGyMaM873SGjRfdi-pfzEhWvTYUrfSiZq-LAbIHAOjpRlk-Ki0sM9cwExfDDPL1d0PtpK5vz8XJgO0qz273c8E3xaq2t8xY2xxwZ29iIHrHJ_jB2b0VtVXYbmKtIe9i2ZjcEEMLG_jxczwTAY9-kw4YLMTqgVcfSicBDoUnflPXGalbOw6OTcTT0yRJLWOpj1UDlHSWFShnr0vvoZ46ZY9FX7w-5tJDh_B7Jj_tjvGFaUbWfL8VZ-UVz1EeBeWePunM3TFNMWqG3zQjZFnC_fvPEJchBV2drqFJTgfqwgTQpVhVuzdnXCw42oUR8l8XR0gaytaXPC7pG7yqh5i2j0ulgHk9h9GPQMvpJW4wYFLEiokTTqvA5vy1Naqdp3QAssO-1fHPwJHME1jWOXVh-GXuXo1HHRXtdTxUJz5Ax2RdrM3hNIO4Ae1mYH2ol0D5liPSXqCu-R7LFEAag2UyYAp7OvuqJEivg0qeN2Q70u2kR0xmJkgNrjb-R-RbamRL0BT8z0olWbgkHysGNLGmBkTRlYQshUC9O_ezaHDSp-Cqa2Ug9TlZT1Y8OsfZNfxwNnYbh_s-FvuTPmlfDoXVnjjoQkm8CevWpfoSAHTCszWWHtlJusBIEJgqAQ