 runs javaTest with the native-image agent, rather than during compilation. I need a test that invokes the macro at runtime, but that could be challenging with the Toolbox's speed limitations.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_rdkCbNgbN6R0BsqpGYYKSkDV|fc_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc2860ce4c819ca316e81fa9e4db45\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.scalameta/parsers_2.13/4.9.3/src/test/scala/org_scalameta/parsers_2_13/ReificationMacrosTest.scala\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 6381, \"output\": 1260, \"cacheRead\": 26112, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 33753, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778133068973, \"responseId\": \"resp_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc284e2bb4819cbb48af402e98d3f5\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_rdkCbNgbN6R0BsqpGYYKSkDV|fc_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc2860ce4c819ca316e81fa9e4db45\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_scalameta.parsers_2_13\\n\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.currentMirror\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe\\nimport scala.tools.reflect.ToolBox\\n\\nclass ReificationMacrosTest {\\n  @Test\\n  def expandScalametaQuasiquotesThroughRuntimeCompiler(): Unit = {\\n    try {\\n      val expandedSyntax: List[String] = compileAndRunQuasiquoteProgram()\\n\\n      assertEquals(List(\\\"triple\\\", \\\"n\\\", \\\"map:triple\\\", \\\"Either:2\\\", \\\"Some:value\\\"), expandedSyntax)\\n    } cat