ht also exceed the time limit. Simplifying the quasiquotes might streamline things significantly. I need to create a dedicated test class for ReificationMacros that efficiently triggers all necessary compile-time macros during the testing. It feels like I’m zeroing in on the core issues.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring test coverage and macros**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering whether including direct quasiquotes and removing the Toolbox could allow the test to pass, but I wonder about dynamic access. Perhaps a dynamic report could be generated by the agent during compileTestScala. I’m also thinking about the remaining call sites from ReificationMacros, since macros during test compilation might not be captured by the agent. It seems the TCK likely runs javaTest with the native-image agent, rather than during compilation. I need a test that invokes the macro at runtime, but that could be challenging with the Toolbox's speed limitations.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_rdkCbNgbN6R0BsqpGYYKSkDV|fc_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc2860ce4c819ca316e81fa9e4db45\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.scalameta/parsers_2.13/4.9.3/src/test/scala/org_scalameta/parsers_2_13/ReificationMacrosTest.scala\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 6381, \"output\": 1260, \"cacheRead\": 26112, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 33753, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778133068973, \"responseId\": \"resp_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc284e2bb4819cbb48af402e98d3f5\"}}\n2052:[tool-exec] start id=call_rdkCbNgbN6R0BsqpGYYKSkDV|fc_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc2860ce4c819ca316e81fa9e4db45 name=read args={\"path\": \"tests/src/org.scalameta/parsers_2.13/4.9.3/src/test/scala/org_scalameta/parsers_2_13/ReificationMacrosTest.scala\"}\n2070:  class ReificationMacrosTest {\n2097:          |    val method: Defn.Def = q\"def triple(n: Int): Int = n * 3\"\n2126:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_rdkCbNgbN6R0BsqpGYYKSkDV|fc_04c3cf33d95e4f3d0169fc2860ce4c819ca316e81fa9e4db45\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_scalameta.parsers_2_13\\n\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\n\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.currentMirror\\nimport scala.reflect.runtime.universe\\nimport scala.tools.reflect.ToolBox\\n\\nclass ReificationMacrosTest {\\n  @Test\\n  def expandScalametaQuasiquotesThroughRuntimeCompiler(): Unit = {\\n    try {\\n      val expandedSyntax: List[String] = compileAndRunQuasiquoteProgram()\\n\\n      assertEquals(List(\\\"triple\\\", \\\"n\\\", \\\"map:triple\\\", \\\"Either:2\\\", \\\"Some:value\\\"), expandedSyntax)\\n    } catch {\\n      case error: Error => verifyUnsupportedNativeImageError(error)\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  private def verifyUnsupportedNativeImageError(error: Error): Unit = {\\n    if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n      throw error\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  private def compileAndRunQuasiquoteProgram(): List[String] = {\\n    val toolBox: ToolBox[universe.type] = currentMirror.mkToolBox()\\n    val source: String =\\n      \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        |import scala.meta._\\n        |import scala.meta.quasiquotes._\\n        |\\n        |object RuntimeQuasiquoteProgram {\\n        |  def run(): List[String] = {\\n        |    val method: Defn.Def = q\\\"def triple(n: Int): Int = n * 3\\\"\\n        |    val term: Term = q\\\"List(1, 2, 3).map(triple)\\\"\\n        |    val tpe: Type